Just walked in to place an order. From the doorway I made eye contact with the man making the food who wasn’t wearing a mask and watched him put his mask on since he saw me staring. Walked right out. No way during a pandemic am I going to get food from a place where the people aren’t wearing masks.  Unfortunate, because I used to enjoy this place.

Was ok but not really Greek (or traditional Greek).  The gyro is doner kebab and was ok but nothing great.  One of the chicken wings still had some feathers on it (but pulled off easily) and we're tasty but again, I've had better.

Greekish food to a formula. The gyros lamb and beef is doner meat and has a reasonable taste. Its a little fatty but not overly so. The buffalo wings are nice although they confused our order and we didn't get the blue cheese. The food was prepared quickly and the service was friendly.

If I could give more stars I would.  I called last minute for catering for a Lunch and Learn literally the night before it's date.  They were able to accommodate for the very next day and even had the food delivered before 1pm!  The food was absolutely amazing and the staff (25 of us) loved every bite!  Will definitely keep them on my list for future events!
